Why
We
Picked
It
SoFi
is
perhaps
best
known
as
a
student
loan
refinance
lender
,
but
it
also
makes
loans
to
undergraduates,
graduate
students,
law
and
business
students
and
parents.
Its
undergraduate
student
loan
product
offers
mostly
industry-standard
features,
plus
a
few
perks:
no
late
fees,
an
interest
rate
discount
of
0.125%
if
your
co-signer
already
uses
another
SoFi
product
and
job
search
help
through
its
career
team.
Extra
Details
Loan
terms:
5,
10
and
15
years
Loan
amounts
available:
$5,000
to
total
cost
of
attendance
Eligibility:
Does
not
disclose
credit
score
or
income
requirements
Forbearance
options:
SoFi
offers
a
specific
Unemployment
Protection
Program
that
allows
borrowers
to
pause
payments
in
three-month
increments,
for
up
to
12
months,
if
laid
off
from
work.
A
separate
forbearance
program
is
also
available
for
borrowers
experiencing
other
types
of
economic
hardship,
such
as
medical
expenses.
Borrowers
can
take
up
to
12
months
total
forbearance,
no
matter
which
program
they
use.
Co-signer
release
policy:
Available
after
24
payments
Pros
Access
to
SoFi
member
benefits,
including
career
coaching
No
late
fees
Interest
rate
estimate
available
without
undergoing
a
hard
credit
check
Cons
Maximum
APR
above
10%
