thresholds,
depending
on
the
student’s
year
in
school.
To
qualify,
first-year
students
must
have
a
minimum
high
school
GPA
of
3.5,
second-year
students
must
have
a
minimum
college
GPA
of
3.0,
juniors
must
have
a
minimum
GPA
of
2.75
and
seniors
must
have
a
minimum
GPA
of
2.5.
Note
that
only
borrowers
in
these
states
can
apply:
Arizona,
Arkansas,
Colorado,
Connecticut,
Florida,
Georgia,
Hawaii,
Illinois,
Indiana,
Kansas,
Maryland,
Massachusetts,
Michigan,
Missouri,
Nebraska,
New
Jersey,
New
Mexico,
New
York,
North
Carolina,
Ohio,
Oregon,
Pennsylvania,
South
Carolina,
Tennessee,
Texas,
Vermont,
Virginia,
West
Virginia
and
Wisconsin.
Forbearance
options:
Up
to
24
months
of
forbearance
allowed
in
90-day
increments.
Borrowers
must
pay
$30
per
month
while
in
forbearance,
which
is
less
generous
than
payment-free
forbearance
that
other
lenders
offer.
But
this
policy
helps
borrowers
avoid
occurring
large
amounts
of
interest.
Co-signer
